cross: Cattleya Brabantiae x Cattleya Pao de Acucar

measurements.description: Three flowers on one 15-cm inflorescence; flowers green overlaid dusty rose-bronze; sepals spotted dark purple, more concentrated on lateral sepals; petals heavily spotted dark purple; reverse of flower heavly spotted dark purple; lip white, side lobes yellow centrally blushed pink, ruffled midlobe flushed bright magenta; substance very firm; texture waxy, lip diamond dust.
